Chelsea remain confident that they will secure the signature of Loic Remy despite Arsenal's dramatic intervention on Saturday night by matching their £8million bid.

Remy's representatives were already in talks with Chelsea and the deal is in its advanced stages.

The price of the transfer fee is not in dispute as Remy has a fixed clause in his contract to leave to join a Champions League team. 

